The paper deals with the capacity of a communication channel, which is a fundamental topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of variational methods is also a common technique in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the autoregressive moving average noise spectrum, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI). The iterative refinement of the receiver's knowledge is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of feedback in communication, which is a topic in networking (cs.NI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
